# Use Internal Astronomical Functions

- **Never** search the web or look up eclipse, moon phase, new moon, or other astronomical data from external sources.
- Calendar calculations in this project already use the functions in `CalendarAPI/Other/astronomicalData.js` (e.g. `getMoonPhase`, `getNewMoon`, `getSolsticeEquinox`, eclipse helpers) to compute correct dates.
- When working on calendar or timekeeping logic, use those internal functions. Do not try to verify or source astronomical data from the internet.
